07:25.028 --> 07:26.529
and have an alibi

07:25.028 --> 07:26.529
for that time,

07:26.571 --> 07:29.157
which means

07:26.571 --> 07:29.157
one of you is lying.

07:29.199 --> 07:30.658
It was Terry.

07:30.700 --> 07:32.202
Thanks for coming by, Dill,

07:30.700 --> 07:32.202
but I got it from here.

07:32.244 --> 07:34.371
You see, Terrence,

07:32.244 --> 07:34.371
I couldn't help but notice

07:34.413 --> 07:36.123
you're not wearing

07:34.413 --> 07:36.123
suspenders today--

07:36.164 --> 07:39.418
odd, considering suspenders

07:36.164 --> 07:39.418
are your entire personality.

07:39.459 --> 07:40.752
Seems a little reductive.

07:40.794 --> 07:42.254
I had a rough childhood,

07:42.296 --> 07:43.797
but I lifted myself up

07:42.296 --> 07:43.797
through arts and athletics--

07:43.838 --> 07:45.548
Ah-buh-buh-buhp.

07:43.838 --> 07:45.548
You're the suspenders guy.

07:45.590 --> 07:48.885
Something felt fishy,

07:45.590 --> 07:48.885
so Jakey went fishing,

07:48.927 --> 07:50.470
and I caught me a fat one.

07:50.511 --> 07:52.055
And look at that--

07:52.097 --> 07:54.557
Terry's suspenders

07:52.097 --> 07:54.557
stuffed into his desk drawer,

07:54.599 --> 07:57.644
and there's glitter on them,

07:54.599 --> 07:57.644
red glitter.

07:58.728 --> 08:00.439
Feels like that deserved

07:58.728 --> 08:00.439
an audible gasp.

08:00.521 --> 08:01.773
-[gasps loudly]

08:00.521 --> 08:01.773
-Thank you, Charles.

08:01.815 --> 08:03.233
You got messy

08:01.815 --> 08:03.233
setting up the prank.

08:03.275 --> 08:04.692
You didn't want

08:03.275 --> 08:04.692
anyone to see.

08:04.734 --> 08:06.194
You put the suspenders

08:04.734 --> 08:06.194
in your desk drawer.

08:06.236 --> 08:07.821
Case closed.

08:07.862 --> 08:09.072
Did you put that folder there

08:07.862 --> 08:09.072
just so you could close it?

08:09.114 --> 08:10.365
Yes, Rosa, obviously.

08:10.407 --> 08:11.616
I didn't do anything.

08:11.658 --> 08:12.742
Well, if you didn't

08:11.658 --> 08:12.742
do anything,

08:12.784 --> 08:14.077
how come the case is closed?

08:14.119 --> 08:15.412
-It's not.

08:14.119 --> 08:15.412
-Hm?

08:15.454 --> 08:16.871
The glitter

08:15.454 --> 08:16.871
on Jeffords' suspenders

08:16.913 --> 08:19.791
is type 9A round red glitter

08:16.913 --> 08:19.791
while the bomb spewed

08:19.833 --> 08:22.002
type 9C round red glitter,

08:19.833 --> 08:22.002
but then I suppose

08:22.043 --> 08:24.296
all round red glitter

08:22.043 --> 08:24.296
looks the same to you.

08:24.338 --> 08:26.547
No.

08:24.338 --> 08:26.547
I know the difference.

08:28.049 --> 08:29.384
-One is bigger?

08:28.049 --> 08:29.384
-Shinier.

08:29.426 --> 08:31.136
-Ah.

08:29.426 --> 08:31.136
-The number refers

08:29.426 --> 08:31.136
to the size.

08:31.178 --> 08:32.846
The letter refers

08:31.178 --> 08:32.846
to its reflective qualities.

08:32.887 --> 08:34.639
Seems like you know a weird

08:32.887 --> 08:34.639
amount about glitter, man.

08:34.681 --> 08:37.434
So good detective work

08:34.681 --> 08:37.434
is weird to you?

08:37.476 --> 08:39.269
Interesting squad

08:37.476 --> 08:39.269
you have here, Raymond.

08:39.311 --> 08:40.895
I didn't choose them.

08:39.311 --> 08:40.895
They were here when I arrived.

08:40.937 --> 08:42.022
Understood.

08:42.063 --> 08:43.440
The real question is

08:42.063 --> 08:43.440
why Jeffords

08:43.482 --> 08:44.816
had glitter on him at all.

08:44.858 --> 08:46.318
Fortunately, I have the answer.

08:46.360 --> 08:48.320
I deduced that he has

08:46.360 --> 08:48.320
three young daughters--

08:48.362 --> 08:49.737
twins and a toddler.

08:49.779 --> 08:51.656
Big deal. You saw the picture

08:49.779 --> 08:51.656
on his desk.

08:51.698 --> 08:53.574
I did, and judging by

08:53.616 --> 08:55.660
the maple trees in

08:53.616 --> 08:55.660
the background of that picture,

08:55.702 --> 08:58.079
it was taken last fall--

08:55.702 --> 08:58.079
probably mid October.

08:58.121 --> 09:00.874
The twins are smiling,

08:58.121 --> 09:00.874
each revealing a missing tooth.

09:00.915 --> 09:03.251
The twin on the right--

09:00.915 --> 09:03.251
let's call her "Twin A."

09:03.293 --> 09:04.752
-That's Cagney.

09:03.293 --> 09:04.752
-Is that relevant?

09:04.794 --> 09:06.171
-It's her name.

09:04.794 --> 09:06.171
-So no.

09:06.213 --> 09:08.006
Twin A is missing

09:06.213 --> 09:08.006
an upper right incisor

09:08.048 --> 09:10.675
while Twin B is missing

09:08.048 --> 09:10.675
a lower left incisor

09:10.717 --> 09:12.844
suggesting that they were seven

09:10.717 --> 09:12.844
when the photo was taken,

09:12.886 --> 09:14.471
which would put them

09:12.886 --> 09:14.471
in second grade.

09:14.513 --> 09:16.306
Spring semester

09:14.513 --> 09:16.306
of second grade is when

09:16.348 --> 09:19.059
the Brooklyn schools

09:16.348 --> 09:19.059
do their solar system unit,

09:19.100 --> 09:20.560
a highlight of which

09:19.100 --> 09:20.560
is constructing

09:20.601 --> 09:22.020
a mobile of the planets.

09:22.062 --> 09:24.772
My hypothesis is that Twin A

09:22.062 --> 09:24.772
and Twin B requested

09:24.814 --> 09:28.527
Daddy's help making Mars

09:24.814 --> 09:28.527
sparkle, hence the red glitter.

09:28.568 --> 09:30.862
Damn, yeah,

09:28.568 --> 09:30.862
that's exactly right.

09:30.904 --> 09:32.239
Just seems like

09:30.904 --> 09:32.239
a very complicated way

09:32.280 --> 09:33.614
-of saying Terry has kids.

09:32.280 --> 09:33.614
-Thank you.

09:33.656 --> 09:34.782
What?

09:34.824 --> 09:36.159
The point is,

09:34.824 --> 09:36.159
Jeffords is innocent,

09:36.201 --> 09:39.037
so I guess it's fair to say

09:36.201 --> 09:39.037
case open.

09:39.079 --> 09:41.081
My God, I have gooseflesh.

09:41.122 --> 09:43.166
So now I'd like to move on

09:41.122 --> 09:43.166
to a real suspect.

09:43.208 --> 09:45.626
I wanna see detective Diaz

09:43.208 --> 09:45.626
in the box.

09:45.668 --> 09:48.338
-[gasps]

09:45.668 --> 09:48.338
-What--don't gasp for him.

09:45.668 --> 09:48.338
What are you doing?

09:48.380 --> 09:50.298
-I'm sorry. It just slipped out.

09:48.380 --> 09:50.298
-Title of your sex tape.

09:50.340 --> 09:51.550
Yeah, it's--obviously...

09:51.591 --> 09:52.633
...it's the title

09:51.591 --> 09:52.633
of his sex tape.

09:52.675 --> 09:54.302
Everyone's taking my stuff.

09:54.344 --> 09:55.970
[tense music]

10:01.142 --> 10:03.019
Dillman never talks first

10:01.142 --> 10:03.019
when he's in the box.

10:03.061 --> 10:06.064
Well, Rosa never initiates

10:03.061 --> 10:06.064
conversation of any kind.

10:06.106 --> 10:07.982
Guys, I really

10:06.106 --> 10:07.982
have to get out of here.

10:08.024 --> 10:10.318
<i>Somebody please say something</i>

10:08.024 --> 10:10.318
<i>to get it started.</i>

10:10.360 --> 10:11.861
-No.

10:10.360 --> 10:11.861
-And there it is.

10:11.903 --> 10:14.030
Now that I have the upper hand,

10:11.903 --> 10:14.030
let's get started.

10:14.072 --> 10:15.907
Stupid Terry

10:14.072 --> 10:15.907
and his stupid kids.

10:15.949 --> 10:18.701
<i>You were the only suspect</i>

10:15.949 --> 10:18.701
<i>who did not go</i> out<i> for lunch,</i>

10:18.743 --> 10:20.412
but if you were eating

10:18.743 --> 10:20.412
at your desk,

10:20.454 --> 10:21.621
how did you not see

10:20.454 --> 10:21.621
the perpetrator

10:21.662 --> 10:23.081
plant the glitter bomb?

10:23.123 --> 10:24.374
I wasn't at my desk.

10:23.123 --> 10:24.374
I was in the break room.

10:24.416 --> 10:25.750
Oh, the break room.

10:24.416 --> 10:25.750
That explains it.

10:25.792 --> 10:27.127
I guess we're done here.

10:27.168 --> 10:29.879
Oh, here it comes--

10:27.168 --> 10:29.879
the Dillman double back.

10:30.671 --> 10:31.965
Just to double back--

10:32.006 --> 10:33.800
Oh, my.

10:32.006 --> 10:33.800
He actually said the words.

10:33.841 --> 10:35.009
What a treat.

10:35.051 --> 10:36.470
<i>If you were</i>

10:35.051 --> 10:36.470
<i>in the break room,</i>

10:36.511 --> 10:38.430
why was the IP address

10:36.511 --> 10:38.430
of your laptop

10:38.472 --> 10:40.765
logged into the Wi-Fi

10:38.472 --> 10:40.765
on the fifth floor?

10:40.807 --> 10:42.434
Fine.

10:42.476 --> 10:44.394
There's an empty office there

10:42.476 --> 10:44.394
where I go to be alone.

10:44.436 --> 10:48.815
Seems innocent enough.

10:44.436 --> 10:48.815
Why would you lie about that?

10:48.856 --> 10:51.485
Maybe because you were up there

10:48.856 --> 10:51.485
assembling a glitter bomb.

10:52.152 --> 10:53.861
[mumbles]

10:53.903 --> 10:56.030
-I'm sorry, I didn't--

10:53.903 --> 10:56.030
-I was watching a soap opera.

10:56.072 --> 10:57.949
It's called<i> Drake's Hollow.</i>

10:56.072 --> 10:57.949
I never miss an episode.

10:57.991 --> 11:00.076
It's my mother's favorite show,

10:57.991 --> 11:00.076
and when things were bad

11:00.118 --> 11:02.579
between us, it was the one thing

11:00.118 --> 11:02.579
that we could still talk about.

11:02.621 --> 11:03.580
Oh, that's sweet.

11:03.622 --> 11:04.872
It is kind of sweet.

11:04.914 --> 11:06.874
Sweet enough to fool

11:04.914 --> 11:06.874
a lesser detective.

11:06.916 --> 11:08.793
What--I wasn't fooled.

11:06.916 --> 11:08.793
Take her away.

11:08.835 --> 11:10.920
If you really watch

11:08.835 --> 11:10.920
<i>Drake's Hollow</i> every day,

11:10.962 --> 11:12.671
you won't mind if I

11:10.962 --> 11:12.671
give you a little quiz.

11:12.713 --> 11:14.715
You see, I've been known

11:12.713 --> 11:14.715
to visit the Hollow myself

11:14.757 --> 11:17.344
from time to time not unlike

11:14.757 --> 11:17.344
Nicholas Van Bronderberg.

11:17.385 --> 11:19.720
Who's the father

11:17.385 --> 11:19.720
of Eliana's twins?

11:19.762 --> 11:20.930
Christian is Jacob's father,

11:20.972 --> 11:22.390
but Joshua was stolen

11:20.972 --> 11:22.390
from the hospital.

11:22.432 --> 11:23.850
His real father

11:22.432 --> 11:23.850
remains unknown.

11:23.891 --> 11:25.226
Who did Joshua

11:23.891 --> 11:25.226
grow up to marry?

11:25.268 --> 11:26.394
First came Sandra,

11:25.268 --> 11:26.394
then there was Brigitte,

11:26.436 --> 11:27.646
but she turned out

11:26.436 --> 11:27.646
to be his sister.

11:27.686 --> 11:29.439
<i>Katherine died</i>

11:27.686 --> 11:29.439
<i>during childbirth,</i>

11:29.481 --> 11:30.898
<i>though it was later revealed</i>

11:29.481 --> 11:30.898
<i>that she was murdered</i>

11:30.940 --> 11:32.150
<i>by Amanda,</i>

11:30.940 --> 11:32.150
<i>Joshua's next wife.</i>

11:32.192 --> 11:33.276
They divorced after Amanda

11:33.318 --> 11:34.569
was sentenced

11:33.318 --> 11:34.569
to the electric chair.

11:34.611 --> 11:36.446
But Joshua rebounded quickly

11:34.611 --> 11:36.446
with Jasmine.

11:36.488 --> 11:38.114
Jasmine was followed by Grace,

11:36.488 --> 11:38.114
the love of his life,

11:38.156 --> 11:39.824
but she had a contract dispute

11:38.156 --> 11:39.824
with the producers

11:39.866 --> 11:41.451
so she was killed

11:39.866 --> 11:41.451
off camera by a snake.

11:41.493 --> 11:42.869
[chuckles]

11:41.493 --> 11:42.869
You messed up.

11:42.910 --> 11:45.038
-You forgot Gwendolyn.

11:42.910 --> 11:45.038
-No, I didn't.

11:45.079 --> 11:47.040
Joshua and Gwendolyn were

11:45.079 --> 11:47.040
technically never married

11:47.081 --> 11:49.792
because that whole season took

11:47.081 --> 11:49.792
place inside Kiki's mind...

11:49.834 --> 11:51.961
[whispering]

11:49.834 --> 11:51.961
While she was in a coma.

11:53.046 --> 11:54.589
<i>Diaz is innocent.</i>

11:54.631 --> 11:56.675
So I guess he was wrong

11:54.631 --> 11:56.675
about Rosa.

11:56.715 --> 11:58.385
Don't worry about Dillman.

11:58.426 --> 12:00.512
He's the best detective

11:58.426 --> 12:00.512
I've ever worked with.

12:00.554 --> 12:02.138
Or you just

12:00.554 --> 12:02.138
keep talking him up

12:02.180 --> 12:04.098
because you don't want us

12:02.180 --> 12:04.098
to notice how weird it is

12:04.140 --> 12:05.600
that you brought in a friend

12:04.140 --> 12:05.600
to work the case.

12:05.642 --> 12:06.893
We're not friends.

12:06.934 --> 12:08.395
My only friends

12:06.934 --> 12:08.395
are James and Julian.

12:08.436 --> 12:10.021
Hurtful, but I still

12:08.436 --> 12:10.021
think it's strange

12:10.063 --> 12:11.523
that you won't let me

12:10.063 --> 12:11.523
run the investigation--

12:11.565 --> 12:12.982
unless, of course,

12:11.565 --> 12:12.982
there's something

12:13.024 --> 12:14.568
-you're scared I might find.

12:13.024 --> 12:14.568
-Excuse me?

12:14.609 --> 12:16.777
Where were you between

12:14.609 --> 12:16.777
12:20 and 12:55?

12:16.819 --> 12:18.238
You aren't

12:16.819 --> 12:18.238
seriously suggesting

12:18.279 --> 12:19.531
that I am the prank man.

12:19.573 --> 12:21.157
It does seem

12:19.573 --> 12:21.157
a little far-fetched, Jake.

12:21.199 --> 12:23.243
I mean, he did just use

12:21.199 --> 12:23.243
the phrase, "prank man."

12:23.284 --> 12:24.661
It's not far-fetched at all.

12:24.703 --> 12:26.913
Holt is not the joyless robot

12:24.703 --> 12:26.913
that he once was.

12:26.954 --> 12:28.747
Is this about the time

12:26.954 --> 12:28.747
I ate a burrito?

12:28.789 --> 12:29.874
I was pressured into it.

12:29.916 --> 12:31.501
Just tell us where

12:29.916 --> 12:31.501
you were at lunch.

12:31.543 --> 12:32.835
Well, if you must know,

12:31.543 --> 12:32.835
I was having lunch with Boyle.

12:32.877 --> 12:34.170
[Jake laughs]

12:32.877 --> 12:34.170
No way.

12:34.212 --> 12:35.505
You two are

12:34.212 --> 12:35.505
the second most unlikely

12:35.547 --> 12:36.881
Nine-Nine lunch combination.

12:36.923 --> 12:38.592
First is anyone

12:36.923 --> 12:38.592
with Hitchcock and Scully.

12:38.633 --> 12:40.218
Second is Holt and Charles.

12:40.260 --> 12:41.553
It is pretty strange.

12:41.595 --> 12:43.388
I mean, obviously

12:41.595 --> 12:43.388
it was uncomfortable,

12:43.430 --> 12:44.556
but it was a work lunch.

12:44.598 --> 12:45.724
Look, it's not

12:44.598 --> 12:45.724
a big deal, guys.

12:45.764 --> 12:47.100
We don't have to talk about it.

12:47.141 --> 12:48.935
I was offering him

12:47.141 --> 12:48.935
the task force position.

12:48.976 --> 12:51.104
Boyle is my choice.

12:51.145 --> 12:53.022
Boyle?

12:53.064 --> 12:53.940
From work?

12:53.981 --> 12:56.526
[chuckles]

12:53.981 --> 12:56.526
Oh.

12:56.568 --> 12:59.446
How great for him...

12:56.568 --> 12:59.446
[laughs] And no one else.

12:59.487 --> 13:01.239
You know what, I just remembered

12:59.487 --> 13:01.239
that I'm late to leave.

13:01.281 --> 13:02.532
Gotta go, bye.

13:04.783 --> 13:06.453
Hey.

13:06.494 --> 13:07.828
I don't understand, Charles.

13:07.870 --> 13:09.414
If Holt already assigned you

13:07.870 --> 13:09.414
to the task force,

13:09.456 --> 13:10.665
why were you helping me

13:09.456 --> 13:10.665
try and get it?

13:10.707 --> 13:13.042
I was planning

13:10.707 --> 13:13.042
on telling Holt no.

13:13.084 --> 13:14.127
What?

13:13.084 --> 13:14.127
That's insane.

13:14.168 --> 13:15.754
It's a huge opportunity.

13:15.794 --> 13:17.838
I know, but I've been meaning

13:15.794 --> 13:17.838
to cut back on hours.

13:17.880 --> 13:19.340
I'm working too much.

13:19.382 --> 13:20.967
It's affecting Nikolaj

13:19.382 --> 13:20.967
at school.

13:21.008 --> 13:22.885
He's been making

13:21.008 --> 13:22.885
so many new friends.

13:22.927 --> 13:24.262
Wait,

13:22.927 --> 13:24.262
isn't that a good thing?

13:24.304 --> 13:25.722
No, he's trying

13:24.304 --> 13:25.722
to get me jealous.

13:25.764 --> 13:26.847
I did the same thing to my dad.

13:26.889 --> 13:28.807
So, Jake, for real.

13:28.849 --> 13:30.143
I'm not gonna take

13:28.849 --> 13:30.143
the assignment.

13:30.184 --> 13:32.019
[sighs]

13:30.184 --> 13:32.019
Okay, I guess that makes sense.

13:32.061 --> 13:34.648
But just promise me you're not

13:32.061 --> 13:34.648
turning it down because of me.

13:34.689 --> 13:36.483
Jake, I promise.

13:36.524 --> 13:37.692
Okay.

13:38.985 --> 13:40.654
Great, well,

13:40.695 --> 13:42.155
if you're turning it down,

13:40.695 --> 13:42.155
that means there's still

13:42.196 --> 13:43.531
an opportunity for me

13:42.196 --> 13:43.531
to solve the case

13:43.573 --> 13:45.199
and prove to Holt

13:43.573 --> 13:45.199
I belong on the task force.

13:45.241 --> 13:47.076
-What task force?

13:45.241 --> 13:47.076
-[surprised grunt]

13:47.118 --> 13:48.745
-How long have you been here?

13:47.118 --> 13:48.745
-Just a few seconds.

13:48.787 --> 13:50.204
But that was

13:48.787 --> 13:50.204
more than enough time

13:50.246 --> 13:51.914
for me to ascertain

13:50.246 --> 13:51.914
everything about you--

13:51.956 --> 13:54.167
As a person, yes, we know.

13:51.956 --> 13:54.167
No one likes a know-it-all.

13:54.208 --> 13:55.669
You're married to one.

13:55.710 --> 13:57.253
<i>-You're</i> married to one.

13:55.710 --> 13:57.253
-Follow me.

13:57.295 --> 13:59.046
I have an important

13:57.295 --> 13:59.046
announcement to make.

14:00.131 --> 14:01.508
[both] Dillman.

14:01.549 --> 14:03.092
May I have everyone's

14:01.549 --> 14:03.092
attention please?

14:03.134 --> 14:05.512
I have solved the

14:03.134 --> 14:05.512
"who has done this."

14:05.553 --> 14:07.430
I know by whom it was done.

14:07.472 --> 14:08.973
-It was Jake Peralta.

14:07.472 --> 14:08.973
-[Jake] What?

14:09.015 --> 14:11.142
That's crazy.

14:09.015 --> 14:11.142
The box was on my desk.

14:11.184 --> 14:12.602
-I'm the victim.

14:11.184 --> 14:12.602
-[Hitchcock] Wrong.

14:12.644 --> 14:14.521
-Scully's the victim.

14:12.644 --> 14:14.521
-Yeah!

14:14.562 --> 14:15.980
You think glitter's gonna taste

14:14.562 --> 14:15.980
like sprinkles, but it doesn't.

14:16.022 --> 14:17.440
-It tastes like blood.

14:16.022 --> 14:17.440
-That is blood.

14:17.482 --> 14:18.817
The glitter's

14:17.482 --> 14:18.817
shredding your tongue.

