15:59.542 --> 16:00.627
It was Dillman!

16:00.668 --> 16:03.337
[scoffs]

16:00.668 --> 16:03.337
I just met you today.

16:03.379 --> 16:05.089
-Why would I do that?

16:03.379 --> 16:05.089
-Good question.

16:05.131 --> 16:08.008
It's because you want Holt

16:05.131 --> 16:08.008
to put you on that task force.

16:08.050 --> 16:10.010
Dillman can't be

16:08.050 --> 16:10.010
on a New York task force.

16:10.052 --> 16:11.805
The SFPD would never

16:10.052 --> 16:11.805
approve it.

16:11.846 --> 16:13.973
Correct, only he's not SFPD.

16:14.014 --> 16:15.391
When you first arrived,

16:14.014 --> 16:15.391
you asked us to check

16:15.433 --> 16:17.393
the fingerprints

16:15.433 --> 16:17.393
against the AFI system,

16:17.435 --> 16:20.104
but that system hasn't

16:17.435 --> 16:20.104
been used in over five years

16:20.146 --> 16:21.522
by any police department.

16:21.564 --> 16:24.901
Well, I used

16:21.564 --> 16:24.901
the AFI system for 20 years.

16:24.943 --> 16:26.945
-I guess I misspoke.

16:24.943 --> 16:26.945
-Oh, misspoke.

16:26.986 --> 16:28.154
I see.

16:26.986 --> 16:28.154
That explains everything.

16:28.195 --> 16:29.656
My apologies.

16:29.697 --> 16:31.741
I'm just gonna

16:29.697 --> 16:31.741
head back on out to exile--

16:31.783 --> 16:33.117
just to double back.

16:33.159 --> 16:34.953
My God.

16:33.159 --> 16:34.953
He's double backing Dillman.

16:34.994 --> 16:36.036
How could the best detective

16:34.994 --> 16:36.036
that Holt's ever worked with

16:36.078 --> 16:37.371
make such a mistake?

16:37.413 --> 16:38.706
I wondered myself,

16:37.413 --> 16:38.706
so I made a few phone calls.

16:38.748 --> 16:41.208
It turns out, Dillman

16:38.748 --> 16:41.208
was fired by the SFPD.

16:41.250 --> 16:42.919
I guess he rubbed the brass

16:41.250 --> 16:42.919
the wrong way.

16:42.961 --> 16:45.212
Not only that, but he's

16:42.961 --> 16:45.212
currently working part time

16:45.254 --> 16:47.256
at Yarn Barn,

16:45.254 --> 16:47.256
a hobby shop in Albany.

16:47.298 --> 16:49.467
I have his manager

16:47.298 --> 16:49.467
on the phone right now.

16:49.509 --> 16:51.719
<i>Frank, what is going on?</i>

16:49.509 --> 16:51.719
<i>You have a shift tonight.</i>

16:51.761 --> 16:53.053
<i>You know I have finals.</i>

16:53.095 --> 16:54.722
[stammers]

16:53.095 --> 16:54.722
I'm so sorry, Alyssa.

16:54.764 --> 16:57.725
I got hung up in the city.

16:54.764 --> 16:57.725
I just lost track of time.

16:57.767 --> 16:59.185
This explains everything.

16:57.767 --> 16:59.185
He's not a great detective.

16:59.226 --> 17:01.312
He's a sad man

16:59.226 --> 17:01.312
working part time

17:01.354 --> 17:03.105
selling crafting supplies.

17:03.147 --> 17:05.984
Okay, fine, yes.

17:03.147 --> 17:05.984
I was fired by the SFPD.

17:06.025 --> 17:07.527
And yes, I contacted Raymond

17:07.568 --> 17:09.153
in hopes of getting on

17:07.568 --> 17:09.153
that task force.

17:09.195 --> 17:11.155
I thought it would be my way

17:09.195 --> 17:11.155
back onto the NYPD.

17:11.197 --> 17:12.615
Oh, my God.

17:11.197 --> 17:12.615
I hate the Yarn Barn.

17:12.657 --> 17:14.492
<i>Really disappointing</i>

17:12.657 --> 17:14.492
<i>to hear, Frank,</i>

17:14.534 --> 17:16.118
Yeah, well you're

17:14.534 --> 17:16.118
a bad manager, Alyssa, okay?

17:16.160 --> 17:18.245
You play favorites and it hurts

17:16.160 --> 17:18.245
to be on the outside.

17:18.287 --> 17:19.497
<i>-You don't even show up to--</i>

17:18.287 --> 17:19.497
-Okay.

17:19.539 --> 17:20.790
I was gonna bring up

17:19.539 --> 17:20.790
the task force

17:20.832 --> 17:22.291
when I had lunch

17:20.832 --> 17:22.291
with Raymond tomorrow,

17:22.333 --> 17:24.794
but when he called about

17:22.333 --> 17:24.794
this case, I thought...

17:24.836 --> 17:26.796
-solving it would seal the deal.

17:24.836 --> 17:26.796
-Which would have been easy

17:26.838 --> 17:29.507
-since you set the whole

17:26.838 --> 17:29.507
thing up to frame me.

17:26.838 --> 17:29.507
-Ridiculous.

17:29.549 --> 17:31.509
Why would I have waited

17:29.549 --> 17:31.509
so long to accuse you?

17:31.551 --> 17:33.093
Because if you solved it

17:31.551 --> 17:33.093
right away, it would've

17:31.551 --> 17:33.093
been too obvious.

17:33.135 --> 17:34.762
He's deflecting

17:33.135 --> 17:34.762
because he's guilty.

17:34.804 --> 17:36.556
Dillman lied about

17:34.804 --> 17:36.556
where he worked.

17:34.804 --> 17:36.556
We can't trust him.

17:36.597 --> 17:37.765
The receipt was

17:36.597 --> 17:37.765
in Peralta's bag.

17:37.807 --> 17:38.975
You're the glitter expert.

17:39.017 --> 17:40.226
Well, you're

17:39.017 --> 17:40.226
the Prankmaster General.

17:40.267 --> 17:42.353
-[both] It was him.

17:40.267 --> 17:42.353
-[siren whoops]

17:42.395 --> 17:44.731
It wasn't either of you,

17:44.772 --> 17:46.941
but I know who it was.

17:46.983 --> 17:48.609
Son of a bitch

17:46.983 --> 17:48.609
stole my bullhorn.

17:51.320 --> 17:53.990
Okay, I'm not 100% sure

17:51.320 --> 17:53.990
this is right,

17:54.032 --> 17:55.783
and maybe

17:54.032 --> 17:55.783
I'm missing something--

17:55.825 --> 17:57.201
Charles, as a veteran

17:55.825 --> 17:57.201
of many big reveals,

17:57.243 --> 17:58.369
can I give you a tip?

17:58.411 --> 18:00.038
-Not so much waffling.

17:58.411 --> 18:00.038
-I agree.

18:00.079 --> 18:01.080
You're not commanding the room.

18:01.121 --> 18:02.790
Let him finish--his way.

18:02.832 --> 18:05.209
-But do pace it up

18:02.832 --> 18:05.209
a bit, Charles.

18:02.832 --> 18:05.209
-Copy that.

18:05.251 --> 18:07.253
So from the beginning,

18:05.251 --> 18:07.253
I was very skeptical

18:07.294 --> 18:09.338
that anyone in our squad

18:07.294 --> 18:09.338
was behind the prank.

18:09.380 --> 18:11.007
-Why didn't you just say that?

18:09.380 --> 18:11.007
-I did, and then you said,

18:11.049 --> 18:12.759
"That's exactly what

18:11.049 --> 18:12.759
a guilty person would say."

18:12.800 --> 18:13.885
Eh, I stand by it.

18:13.927 --> 18:15.929
Okay, so who was

18:13.927 --> 18:15.929
the prank man?

18:15.970 --> 18:16.930
There was no prank.

18:16.971 --> 18:18.264
That was just a cover.

18:18.305 --> 18:20.850
You see, guys,

18:18.305 --> 18:20.850
the point of the explosion

18:20.892 --> 18:24.144
was to contaminate the evidence

18:20.892 --> 18:24.144
of the Dekalb Street murder.

18:24.186 --> 18:26.439
But the suspect is in prison,

18:24.186 --> 18:26.439
has no ties to organized crime,

18:26.480 --> 18:27.899
and no means of

18:26.480 --> 18:27.899
bribing an officer.

18:27.941 --> 18:29.525
How could he have possibly

18:27.941 --> 18:29.525
pulled that off?

18:29.567 --> 18:31.193
Yeah, Jake, that stumped me

18:29.567 --> 18:31.193
for a little bit too,

18:31.235 --> 18:33.446
but then something you said

18:31.235 --> 18:33.446
gave me an idea.

18:33.487 --> 18:35.489
I mean, that kind of evidence

18:33.487 --> 18:35.489
would never hold up at trial.

18:35.531 --> 18:36.866
You'd be laughed out of court.

18:36.908 --> 18:38.242
Ah, yeah,

18:36.908 --> 18:38.242
I remember when I said that.

18:38.284 --> 18:39.911
It was awesome.

18:38.284 --> 18:39.911
Wait, but who did it?

18:39.953 --> 18:42.162
The mastermind

18:39.953 --> 18:42.162
was ADA Greene.

18:42.204 --> 18:44.082
He didn't have enough evidence

18:42.204 --> 18:44.082
for the case.

18:44.123 --> 18:45.332
He was afraid

18:44.123 --> 18:45.332
he was gonna lose

18:45.374 --> 18:47.001
and needed someone

18:45.374 --> 18:47.001
to blame it on.

18:47.043 --> 18:48.294
Whom did he work with--

18:48.335 --> 18:50.088
obviously someone who knew

18:48.335 --> 18:50.088
about the pranks

18:50.129 --> 18:52.298
and that Amy called Jake

18:50.129 --> 18:52.298
"babe."

18:52.339 --> 18:53.800
Excellent question, Captain.

18:53.841 --> 18:54.968
It took a little digging

18:53.841 --> 18:54.968
to find that out,

18:55.009 --> 18:56.343
but I pulled some

18:55.009 --> 18:56.343
personnel files

18:56.385 --> 18:58.387
and combed through

18:56.385 --> 18:58.387
some social media.

18:58.429 --> 19:00.347
Do you know what Greene's

18:58.429 --> 19:00.347
wife's maiden name is?

19:00.389 --> 19:01.474
-Duchovny?

19:00.389 --> 19:01.474
-No.

19:01.515 --> 19:02.558
-Zappa.

19:01.515 --> 19:02.558
-No.

19:02.600 --> 19:04.143
-Fagerbakke.

19:02.600 --> 19:04.143
-No, Booth.

19:04.184 --> 19:05.979
Howard Booth,

19:06.020 --> 19:07.063
as in, Officer Booth.

19:07.105 --> 19:09.273
Oh, yes.

19:07.105 --> 19:09.273
Officer Howard.

19:09.315 --> 19:10.775
He's Greene's brother-in-law.

19:10.817 --> 19:12.652
He didn't just put the evidence

19:10.817 --> 19:12.652
on Jake's desk.

19:12.693 --> 19:14.654
-He put the glitter bomb there.

19:12.693 --> 19:14.654
-Oh, my God.

19:14.695 --> 19:16.906
-We have to find Booth.

19:14.695 --> 19:16.906
-Already did it.

19:16.948 --> 19:18.365
And I booked him.

19:18.407 --> 19:21.327
-[elevator dings]

19:18.407 --> 19:21.327
-Oh, classic elevator reveal.

19:21.368 --> 19:23.037
This feels like it calls

19:21.368 --> 19:23.037
for an audible gasp.

19:23.079 --> 19:24.497
-[Charles gasps loudly]

19:23.079 --> 19:24.497
-Not from you, Charles.

19:24.538 --> 19:25.665
From me.

19:24.538 --> 19:25.665
[gasps loudly]

19:25.706 --> 19:26.874
[gasps loudly]

19:26.916 --> 19:28.126
Wait, did you just

19:26.916 --> 19:28.126
gasp at my gasp?

19:28.167 --> 19:30.086
Sorry.

19:28.167 --> 19:30.086
Your gasp was so good.

19:30.128 --> 19:31.587
Oh, thank you for gasping

19:30.128 --> 19:31.587
at my gasp.

19:31.629 --> 19:33.213
My pleasure.

19:34.381 --> 19:35.758
Sorry you missed

19:34.381 --> 19:35.758
your daughter's concert.

19:35.800 --> 19:37.093
No, no, it's okay.

19:37.135 --> 19:38.886
Sharon totally understood--

19:38.928 --> 19:40.847
after I lied to her

19:38.928 --> 19:40.847
and said we had to stay late

19:40.888 --> 19:42.056
because Rosa got shot.

19:42.098 --> 19:43.891
Next time you see her,

19:42.098 --> 19:43.891
walk with a limp.

19:43.933 --> 19:45.184
Copy that.

19:45.225 --> 19:46.769
[Jake] Hey,

19:46.811 --> 19:47.770
you know you don't

19:46.811 --> 19:47.770
have to sweep up, right?

19:47.812 --> 19:49.188
Well, someone's gotta.

19:49.229 --> 19:50.731
Plus it reminds me

19:49.229 --> 19:50.731
of the three years I spent

19:50.773 --> 19:52.316
as a cleaning lady in college.

19:52.358 --> 19:54.527
Huh, I guess there really

19:52.358 --> 19:54.527
is no term for cleaning man.

19:54.568 --> 19:56.320
-Mm-mm.

19:54.568 --> 19:56.320
-That's not great.

19:56.362 --> 19:57.864
So hey, listen.

19:57.905 --> 20:00.449
I wanted to say great job today

19:57.905 --> 20:00.449
and also I'm sorry.

20:00.491 --> 20:01.742
Sorry for what?

20:01.784 --> 20:03.161
Well, when I heard

20:01.784 --> 20:03.161
you got the task force,

20:03.202 --> 20:04.912
my first reaction was just

20:03.202 --> 20:04.912
to feel sad for myself

20:04.954 --> 20:06.039
instead of happy for you.

20:06.080 --> 20:08.124
Well, you sure hid it well.

20:08.166 --> 20:09.542
I really didn't.

20:09.583 --> 20:11.251
I stormed into the other room

20:09.583 --> 20:11.251
and moped by myself.

20:11.293 --> 20:12.252
Eh, but you had style.

20:12.294 --> 20:14.547
Charles, no.

20:12.294 --> 20:14.547
Look.

20:14.588 --> 20:16.465
You have to take

20:14.588 --> 20:16.465
the task force job.

20:16.507 --> 20:18.676
Really?

20:16.507 --> 20:18.676
What about Nikolaj?

20:18.718 --> 20:20.386
He's gonna be so proud

20:18.718 --> 20:20.386
of his dad.

20:20.427 --> 20:22.055
I bet he even ditches

20:20.427 --> 20:22.055
those new friends.

20:22.096 --> 20:24.098
Oh, man.

20:22.096 --> 20:24.098
That's the dream.

20:24.140 --> 20:26.266
Thank you for saying that.

20:24.140 --> 20:26.266
Honestly, though,

20:26.308 --> 20:27.894
I still don't get why

20:26.308 --> 20:27.894
Holt chose me over you.

20:27.935 --> 20:29.311
Are you kidding?

20:29.353 --> 20:30.521
I mean, just look at today.

20:30.563 --> 20:32.439
Instead of fighting

20:30.563 --> 20:32.439
for attention,

20:32.481 --> 20:34.441
you did the work and

20:32.481 --> 20:34.441
methodically built your case.

20:34.483 --> 20:37.195
You noticed things

20:34.483 --> 20:37.195
that a room full of

20:34.483 --> 20:37.195
seasoned cops all missed.

20:37.236 --> 20:38.946
You're a great detective,

20:37.236 --> 20:38.946
Charles.

20:38.988 --> 20:40.406
Wow.

20:40.447 --> 20:43.450
Even in defeat,

20:40.447 --> 20:43.450
you are a true prince of a man.

20:43.492 --> 20:45.285
-The task force is yours.

20:43.492 --> 20:45.285
-What? No.

20:45.327 --> 20:46.579
Boyle, just take the win!

20:46.620 --> 20:48.622
-Right.

20:46.620 --> 20:48.622
-It was good to see you today.

20:48.664 --> 20:50.958
I'll keep my ears open for any

20:48.664 --> 20:50.958
job opportunities that arise.

20:51.000 --> 20:53.211
Appreciate it.

20:51.000 --> 20:53.211
I could use it.

